# pkgids

Safe package detonation and analysis toolkit. Fetch a package from a public registry, run it inside an isolated sandbox, capture its runtime behaviour, and produce a maliciousness score with a structured report.

## Supported ecosystems

| Ecosystem | Registry |
|-----------|----------|
| `pypi`    | pypi.org |
| `npm`     | npmjs.com |

## Quick start

```bash
# create venv and install
python -m venv .venv
.venv\Scripts\pip install -e .
.venv\Scripts\pip install pytest

# run a detonate job (skeleton — no real detonation yet)
pkgids detonate pypi requests 2.31.0

# run tests
pytest -v
```

## CLI reference

```
pkgids detonate <ecosystem> <name> <version>
```

Validates the ecosystem, prints the job as JSON, and exits 0.
Exits non-zero with a descriptive error if the ecosystem is unsupported.

## Configuration

Edit `config.toml` to adjust paths, sandbox image, timeouts, and scoring thresholds.

## Architecture

```
fetch   →  sandbox  →  capture  →  analyze  →  score  →  report
```

All pipeline stages are stubs pending full implementation.
